commit.message: Add/Fix: Translators for certain window parameters

Fix: (burly-bookmark-names) Load default bookmarks file when needed

Fixes #46.

Fix: cl-etypecase form

Don't know how this wasn't caught sooner.  I guess Emacs 29's
byte-compiler gained a new check, and apparently it never hit that
code path in use.

Fix: (burly-follow-url-org-mode) Don't rebind alist-get

While it worked fine before, an innocent change in Org 9.6 was broken
by this (because ALIST-GET was rebound for the entire downstream call
stack).  The fancy use of CL-LETF and PCASE-LET was too fancy.  It was
a bad idea in the first place, and I hope I reemmber not to make this
mistake again.

Lisp: As they say, "With great power comes great responsibility."

With thanks to Ihor Radchenko (@yantar92) for debugging.

Change: (burly--frameset-restore) Attempted workaround for errors

In case of an error that occurs while restoring a frameset (like an
inexplicable "Cannot resize window" error), we show a warning instead
of signaling the error.  Hopefully this will allow partial
functionality and encourage the user to report the problem.

Fix: (burly--bookmark-url-buffer) Add workaround for Emacs bug

See <https://debbugs.gnu.org/cgi/bugreport.cgi?bug=56643>.

Change: Require Emacs 27.1 or later

But require 28.1 or later for burly-tabs-mode, which has some relevant
fixes in tab-bar-mode.

See #16.  Thanks to @rswgnu for suggesting.

Change: (burly-url-buffer) Workaround for unfound buffer names

If a buffer can't be found by name, rather than returning nil (which
bubbles up and causes an error when Emacs tries to put the window
state), make a buffer explaining the problem and return it.

This kind of error usually represents a bug in the mode of the buffer
that was bookmarked (i.e. a bad or missing
bookmark-make-record-function) rather than in Burly itself, and we
don't want that to abort the opening of other buffers/windows for the
bookmark.

Merge: burly-tabs
